smalgol-.wprior to and during the  western jointcomputer conference, several people in the joint users groups had expressed interest in defining a "smalgol"language.  this is to be an algol language for use with compilers on relatively small size computers. a preliminary report resulted.  at the acm national conference four months later, after consideringseveral counter proposals, a final version was agreed upon by a subcommittee.  the recommendationsof the subcommittee for a standard subset of algol  for use on small computers is presented here.cacm november, bachelork, g. a.dempster, j. r. h.knuth, d. e.speroni, j.ca jb march ,   : pm